    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>Fort's correspondence discusses the submission of 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">God and the Fishmonger</title>to his
         publishers, and Victor Gollancz's rejection of 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Wild Talents</title>; the founding of
         the Fortean society; 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>and the reviews it has
         received; and research into occult powers. Tiffany Thayer
         comments on dianetics and L. Ron Hubbard; Fort comments on
         Irving Babbitt and Baron Karl Von Reichenbach.</p>
      <p>Collection also includes clippings from American and
         foreign newspapers and magazines re 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Book of the Damned</title>, 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">New Lands</title>, 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>, and 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Wild Talents</title>; printed letters
         and circulars re 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>and 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Wild Talents</title>; pamphlets and
         application forms for the Fortean Society; and a typescript
         with corrections of 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>.</p>
      <p>Correspondents include Curtis Brown, Ltd.; Nelson Bond;
         Ruth D'Agostino; Martin Kamin; Claude Kendall; Aaron Sussman;
         Monroe Upton; Nathan Wallack; and Tiffany Thayer.</p>
    </scopecontent>
