        <c02 level="item" id="d1e227">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Elmer Ellsworth, Jr. [Tiffany Thayer] to
                  (carbon) Charles Fort 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1930 Apr 29</unitdate></unittitle>
            <physdesc>TL. 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Has read part of 
                  <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">God and the
                  Fishmonger</title>and has submitted it to his
                  publisher. Comments on the work.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e241">
          <did>
            <unittitle>T. T. to Mr. Cope [encl. 3 clippings and
                  10 copies of form letter re Fortean Society] 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1931 Jan 22</unitdate></unittitle>
            <physdesc>TL. 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Offers enclosed information re Fortean Society.
                  Mentions some new members, Alexander Woollcott, Harry
                  Leon Wilson, Charles G. Norris. Form letter, dated 21
                  Jan 1931 announces first meeting of Fortean Society
                  with founder members.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e252">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Monroe Upton to Claude Kendall [encl. 3 p.
                  TMs (carbon) of Upton review of 
                  <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>] 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1931 Feb 25</unitdate></unittitle>
            <physdesc>TLS. 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Thanks for copy of 
                  <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>Sends enclosed
                  review, and reports on friends' acquaintance with the
                  book. Offers to advertise other books.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e269">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Martin Kamin to Aaron Sussman [encl. 1 p.
                  invitation to the Fortean Society] 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1931 Mar 12</unitdate></unittitle>
            <physdesc>TLS. 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Requests display material and ten copies of first
                  edition of 
                  <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e283">
          <did>
            <unittitle>[Curtis Brown, Ltd.] to A. S. (carbon) 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1932 Apr 28</unitdate></unittitle>
            <physdesc>TLS. 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Reports that Messrs. Victor Gollancz have declined
                  <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Wild Talents</title>.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e297">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Ruth D'Agostico to A. S. 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">n. d.</unitdate></unittitle>
            <physdesc>TLS. 1 p.</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Requests an appointment with Miss Brown. Enthuses
                  over 
                  <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Lo!</title>.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
